The data moat is the real defensibility — every student who completes a project generates verified skill data that companies pay to access. The more students, the more valuable the hiring pipeline becomes.

The One-Line Pitch
"CodeCraft turns final-year engineering students into job-ready developers by simulating their first job before they ever apply for one."

Founder's Unfair Advantage to Build This
The problem is real, measurable (Severity 9), and the market is massive — India alone produces 15 lakh engineering graduates per year. Even capturing 1% of that at ₹1,200/month is a ₹180 Cr/year market from students alone, before touching the B2B side.

The insight that colleges won't be disrupted but can be partnered with is the key to distribution at scale without massive CAC.

